LINE.Text: A NEW REPORT SHOWS THAT 1,440 M LITRES OF BIOFUEL WAS
SUPPLIED IN THE UK IN 2011 UNDER AN INITIATIVE TO CUT DOWN
GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS FROM ROAD TRANSPORT.
THE RENEWABLE TRANSPORT FUEL OBLIGATION WAS SET UP TO GET THE UK GUZZLING
MORE EENVIRONMENTALLY-FRIENDLY FUELS LIKE COOKING OIL AND SOY. UNDER THE RTFO,
A HUGE 4.3 BILLION LITRES OF BIOFUEL HAVE BEEN SUPPLIED IN THE FIRST 36 MONTHS,
WITH THE LARGEST PROPORTION COMING FROM COOKING OIL. THE UK MANAGED TO GO 8%
OVER TARGET ON GREENHOUSE GAS SAVINGS, HOWEVER ONLY 55% OF BIOFUELS MET ENVIRONMENTAL
STANDARD. COMPARED TO THE 80% TARGET. THIS INFOGRAPHIC VISUALLY BREAKS
DOWN THE MAIN FINDINGS FROM THE REPORT.
